[1] Case updates
- Fri 21 Dec 2018. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=20fedfa6d0

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 20 Dec 2018:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 563, of which 515 are confirmed and 48 are probable. In total, there have been 343 deaths (295 in confirmed and 48 in probable cases) and 195 people have recovered.
- 81 suspected cases are under investigation.
- 3 new confirmed cases, including 1 in Beni, 1 in Komanda and 1 in Oicha.
- 7 new confirmed case deaths, 2 in Beni (1 community death), 2 in Butembo, 1 in Mabalako, 1 in Komanda (1 community death), and 1 in Oicha (1 community death).
- 2 new people recovered and were discharged from the Butembo Ebola treatment center (ETC).

News of the response
Vaccination
-----------
- Continued wide-belt vaccination (or ring plus) in Otomaber (in Komanda Health Zone) and Aloya (in Mabalako Health Zone).
- Continued immunization of primary care providers in the Goma Health Zone.
- Since the beginning of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018, 50 489 people have been vaccinated, including 19 147 in Beni [North Kivu], 9519 in Katwa [North Kivu], 5428 in Butembo [North Kivu], 5261 in Mabalako [North Kivu], 2221 in Kalunguta [North Kivu], 1663 in Mandima [Ituri], 1029 in Komanda [Ituri], 861 in Oicha [North Kivu], 791 in Vuhovi [North Kivu], 750 in Masereka [North Kivu], 700 in Lubero [North Kivu], 659 in Kyondo [Uganda], 599 in Mutwanga [North Kivu], 569 in Goma [North Kivu], 434 in Bunia [Ituri], 355 in Tchomia [Ituri], 344 in Musienene [North Kivu], 70 in Biena [North Kivu], 63 in Alimbongo [North Kivu], 13 in Karisimbi [North Kivu] and 13 in Kisangani [Tshopo].
- The only vaccine to be used in this outbreak is the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine, manufactured by the pharmaceutical group Merck, following approval by the Ethics Committee in its decision of 19 May 2018.
- See the source URL for table showing the epidemiologic situation of Ebola virus disease by province and health zone, confirmed cases, probable cases, and total; and confirmed deaths and total; and suspect cases.
- Also see the source URL for figure depicting a map of the history of Ebola epidemics in the DRC.

--
